WYRMFLOW END USER LICENSE AGREEMENT

Last updated: 2026-05-13

PLEASE READ THIS AGREEMENT CAREFULLY BEFORE INSTALLING OR USING WYRMFLOW.
BY INSTALLING OR USING THE SOFTWARE YOU AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THESE TERMS.
IF YOU DO NOT AGREE, DO NOT INSTALL OR USE THE SOFTWARE.

---

1. DEFINITIONS

"Software" means the Wyrmflow desktop application and all associated files
distributed under this Agreement.

"Licensee" means the individual who installs or uses the Software.

"Free Tier" means use of the Software against one (1) locally-cloned
repository per machine at no charge.

"Paid Tier" means a subscription purchased at wyrmflow.com/pricing that
unlocks use of the Software against more than one repository.

"Repository" means a directory that contains a Jujutsu (.jj) or Git (.git)
version-control database opened by the Software.

---

2. GRANT OF LICENSE

Subject to the terms of this Agreement, the developer of Wyrmflow grants
Licensee a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to:

  (a) Install and use the Software on devices owned or controlled by Licensee;
  (b) Under the Free Tier: use the Software against ONE (1) open Repository
      per machine at any given time at no charge;
  (c) Under an active Paid Tier subscription: use the Software against an
      unlimited number of Repositories per the terms of that subscription.

---

3. RESTRICTIONS

Licensee may not:

  (a) Redistribute, sublicense, sell, rent, lease, or otherwise transfer the
      Software or any rights in it to any third party;
  (b) Reverse-engineer, decompile, disassemble, or attempt to derive the
      source code of the Software, except to the limited extent permitted by
      applicable law;
  (c) Remove or alter any proprietary notices, labels, or marks in the
      Software;
  (d) Bypass or disable any licensing, update, or telemetry mechanisms
      without an active Paid Tier subscription.

---

4. AUTOMATIC UPDATES

The Software may check for and apply updates automatically. Licensee may
disable automatic updates in the Software's Settings. Continued use of the
Software after an update constitutes acceptance of the updated version.

---

5. TELEMETRY

The Software may collect anonymous usage data to improve the product.
Collection is disclosed in the Software's privacy settings and may be
disabled. No personally identifiable information is collected without
explicit consent.

---

6. TERMINATION

This license is effective until terminated. It will terminate automatically
without notice if Licensee breaches any term of this Agreement. Upon
termination Licensee must cease all use of the Software and destroy all
copies in their possession.

